column2: W wind 0-5 mph- 60% clouds- no rain past 24 hours.
N wind 5-10 mph- 50% clouds- reading during sun
Partly cloudy- calm- 1 surviving loon chick first in 3 years.
Sky clear- water cloudy- wind calm- been in England past month.  Lake level: very high
Clouds 50%- W wind 15 mph- air 44 F.  Lake level: very high
Clouds 10%- NE wind 10 mph- air 38 F- depth at site 63'
5 to 10% cloud cover- east wind: 15 to 20 mph- 3" of rain in last 2 weeks.
S wind at 10 mph- hazy- clear
Algae- 3.43" rain since 6/28- partly cloudy- SW winds at 10mph- heavy rainfall this year
E wind at 5 mph- clear- above average rain this year- no mating loons
Southwest wind at 10-15 mph- clear- black specks falling from sky daily
S wind at 5 mph- clear- particles in water
Southwest wind at 5-10 mph- clear- thin clouds- particles in water- more rain than normal this month
Cold- calm- clear- particles in water- fallout on white rowing shell reduced last week
Clear- SW wind at 10 mph- 40 F
Clear-  W wind at 10 mph- 55 F- particles suspended in water
Thin clouds- light winds. air temp: 80.
Loons and Canada geese are nesting- bald eagle feeding young. clear- blue skies- air temp: 65.
High thin clouds- light winds- air temp: 55.
Southwest wind at 5-10 mph- high thin clouds in the sky- eagles nest with a baby eaglet flexing his wings- and the presence of two loons indicate they are not nesting.
Clear sky- northwest wind at 10 mph- particles in suspension in water- witnessed male mudfish herding a 8" glob of black 1" fingerlings.  Mudfish about 18" long and 2" wide.
Particles in suspension in water- sky clear- water calm.
Partly cloudy- northeast wind most of the week- no particles and 2.3 inches of rain.
Sky- high thin clouds- winds- 5-10 mph northwest- no particles in the water.
Wind is calm- sky is clear.
Wind: 10 mph from west- sky: tested during a break in the clouds.
Wind: 10 mph from the west- sky: clear.
Sky is clear- wind is 10-15 mph from SE- particles in the water- anchor came up clean- as always.
Sky is clear- wind @ 10 mph from the south- particles in the water.
Sky is clear- wind from NE 10-15 mph- particles in the water.
Sky-high thin clouds- wind- west 10 mph- particles in water.
Sky is clear- wind is 10-15 mph from the north.
Clear sky- calm winds- anchor came up clean- first loon arrived first day after ice out.
Suspended green particles- clear sky- west wind 5 mph- anchor came up clean
S wind 10 mph- clear sky- suspended particles in water- 1.72" of rain in last 4 days
Clear sky- some particles in water.
Clear- very windy- air temp 55 at 5 a.m.  Lake level: very high
Wind- south @ 10 mph.  Sky - high thin clouds.
Temperature is 58 degrees- skies clear- brisk breeze- .25" of rain yesterday afternoon.
Had trouble getting sampler to close- south wind @ 20 mph- clear sky at time of secchi
Particles in water- clear sky- west wind 10 mph.
Water calm- sky-test during break in clouds.
Test during break in clouds.  West wind 10 mph.
West wind 10 mph- test during break in clouds.
Calm water- clear sky- no loon family this year- lots of single loons.
Skies clear- bright.  Slight breeze- very windy in the last 2 days- temp is 53 degrees at 8 am.  There are some particles.
Calm water- clear sky but hazy- particles in water.
Clear sky- N wind @ 10 mph- particles in water.
Clear sky- winds are calm- particles in the water.
Sky is clear- wind is 10 mph @ W- particles in the water- received 4.65" of rain in the last 4 days.
Clear sky- calm winds- some particles in the water.
Clear sky- south wind- 10 mph- some particles- two loons still on the lake.
High thin haze- bright sun- east wind @ 5-10 mph- temp is 45 degrees at 8 am.

Ice out on 4/21/1995.  Bright and hazy- the air temperature is 45 degrees at 7:00am- calm wind- pair of eagles with one carrying a fish- flew over- calling as they approached nest at southeast corner of lake.
2.3" of rain since last test on 5/6/95.  The west wind is 15 mph and there are clear skies.
Northeast wind at 5-10 mph- high thin clouds in the sky- and 0.14" of rain since last test.
Clear sky- north wind at 5 mph- 0.14" of rain since last test- and baby crow on ground near cabin- can't fly yet.
Clear sky- calm- two geese and five goslings on north shore- one inch of rain since last reading.
Clear sky and south wind at 15 mph.
High thin clouds- wind-5 mph from south- no rain in two weeks.
High thin clouds- west wind 10 mph- no rain since last week.
Sky high thin clouds- wind south east 5-10 mph- 2.25" rain since 7/7/95.
Clear sky and south wind at 15 mph.
Clear sky- west wind @ 10 mph- 0.50" rain in last 24 hours +1.10" since 7/14/95.
Had 6" of rain in July and 25" of rain in August.
Ice out 4/28 + 29.  Spring at least 2 weeks late. hepatica- traveling arbutus just blooming.  A few lonely warblers (yellow rump- pine) wandering through.  Temp 7 am 35 F. 51 F at 1 pm.
West wind 15 mph.  Clear sky.  Cold temperature.  Lake level: very high
Cold- clear sky- and west wind at 5 mph.
Beautiful calm day- clear- blue skies. " What is so rare as a day in June "  45 F at 6 am- 78 F at 2 pm.
Clear sky.  Calm wind.  Pinhead or smaller particles in water.
5" rain two days ago. Clear sky. West wind 15 mph.
Clear sky.  Water calm.  Lake level: very high
Clear sky.  Winds south 15 mph. 10" rain in last month. forest is lush.  Lake level: very high
48 F at 8 am. Very little rain in last month. Beautiful fall day. Colors at peak.
64 degrees at noon.  Very still- high thin clouds.  Glorious day.
Air very still and humid.  Rain gauge reading on 7/25/97 = 2.5 inches.
High thin clouds- W wind 5 mph.
South wind at 10-15 mph- clear skies- high water level
South wind at 10 mph- high thin clouds- water level is still high
The temperature is 58 degrees- light breeze from southwest at 10 mph- clear sky- temperature yesterday in low 80's and there has been no rain for the past 2 weeks.
Cold water- NE wind 5 mph- clear sky.
NW wind 10 mph- clear sky- particles in water.
S wind 10 mph- clear sky- particles in water.
Clear sky- S wind 10 mph- 2 adult eagles overhead.
Clear sky- west wind at 10 mph- cold water.
Clear sky- southwest wind at 5-10 mph.
Clear sky- west wind at 5 mph.
Clear- S wind 5-10 mph- 5.5" rain so far in August- 5.5" rain in July
High thin clouds- E wind 15 mph.
Test between clouds - W wind 10 mph- air temp in low 40's (cold hands)
Clear sky- north wind at 5-10 mph.
With grand niece- Haley Stewart (age 7 1/2)- clear sky- west wind at 5 mph- 1.1" of rain in the last 24 hours.
Clear sky and west wind at 10-15 mph.
South wind at 10 mph and clear sky.
North wind at 10-15 mph- clear sky between clouds- and two geese and six goslings on south side.
West wind at 10 mph and clear sky.
Monitored with grand niece- Haley Stewart.  Calm and clear sky.
Clear sky and northeast wind at 5 mph.
South wind at 5 mph and clear sky.
North wind 10-15 mph. Clear sky. 2 loons diving.
South wind 10 mph. Clear- hazy sky. Hot and humid.
East wind about 10 mph. Clear sky. 5.71 inches of rain in last 3 days.
West wind about 5 mph. Clear sky. 3/4 inches of rain the day before.
Clear- calm- particles in water. Drowned person has not floated. Drowned 8/15/02.
South wind 10 mph. High thin clouds. 5.5" rain during last wek. Very high water level.
Clear sky- calm. 1" rain during last week. Rowed to sample site.
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
Reading corrected for 4 ft rail on pontoon.  Particles in water; Pollen on surface- calm clear sky- adult eagle flying.
Rail correction. SW wind 15-20 mph.  Clear sky.  Over 2" rain in past week.
Rail correction. SW wind 10 mph.  Clear sky.
Rail correction. NE wind 5 mph. Clear sky. Cata collectors: Kent Dickerman and Marshall Thompson- Blaine Darrah- Toni Ventenbergs.
South wind 5 mph.  Clear sky. Rail correction.
Loon.  Test between clouds.  Wind southwest 5 mph.  Rail correction.  Data collectors: John Darrah- Sam VanWetter- Sampson Darrah- Issabela D.- Walker Stewert- Jesse and Jared Colin- Chris D.
West wind 10 mph.  Clear sky.  4 geese flying.  4 ft to water surface rail correction.
Calm- high thin clouds.  4 ft rail correction.
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
West wind 10 mph.  Test between clouds.
Clear sky- SE wind 5 mph.  Four loons (includes two babies)
High thin clouds.  South wind 10 mph.
SW wind 10-15 mph.  Clear sky.  Less than 1/2" rain since 7/1/2005.  Only one baby loon remains.
NE wind 5 mph.  Mother and baby loon on lake.  Clear sky.
slight breeze- recent rain- Mark Bixby helper
clear and cool- Mark Bixby helper clear and cool- Mark Bixby helper
scattered clouds- fresh breeze- Mark Bixby helper scattered clouds- fresh breeze- unseasonably cool summer so far.  Mark Bixby helper
high clouds- fair- cool- Mark Bixby helper
warm and sunny- recent rain- Mark Bixby helper
Mark Bixby was my helper. It was a windy day.
Mark Bixby was my helper. It was a windy day.
A late spring for the first reading. Rain the night before- scattered clouds- blueberries blooming. Beaufort 3- 65 degrees F.
No Blueberries! Did all the blossoms blow off in the huge storm July 1  Trees down everywhere--enormous damage to the forests.
Light haze- nice fall day- Beaufort 1

Hot summer day- a bit hazy because of wildfires to west- still. Some boat activity. Accompanied by Mark Bixby and Tina Juliana and Angel Hillstrom  We were glad to see the clarity improved. It had declined quite a bit last year.
Scattered clouds- 85 degrees- calm but some boat traffic. Mark Bixby is my helper.
High haze- light breeze- scattered cirrostratus clouds

light breeze- air temperature 70 degrees- water temperature 66 degrees
